\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 What is the Key Usage Extension?
\f1\b0 \
The Key Usage Extension (KUE) defines how a certificate can be used. You can use a key usage extension to limit which operations the public key in a certificate can perform. For example, you could create a certificate to sign emails, but not to encrypt them. The Extended Key Usage certificate (EKU) is similar to the KUE, but it defines a certificate in terms of \'93purpose\'94 (for example, to sign OCSP responses, identify an SSL client and so on). The EKU is newer and more extensible than the KUE, so it is often considered \'93the\'94 usage-restriction mechanism. You can configure the Extended Key Usage extension later in this assistant.\
\
