\f0\b \cf0 What does \'93This extension is critical\'94 mean?
\f1\b0 \
This is also known as the \'93criticality indicator\'94. It is a flag that instructs software which uses the certificate whether it is safe to ignore the Key Usage Extension if it does not recognise it. A certificate will be rejected if the software does not recognise a \'93critical extension\'94.}